description: From Italian atterrare. Compare Late Latin atterrare (“to cast to earth”).

verbs.description: atterrate (third-person singular simple present atterrates, present participle atterrating, simple past and past participle atterrated)

entries.meaning: (obsolete, rare, transitive) To fill up with alluvial earth.
examples: The rain doth […] atterrate or add part of the sea to the firm land
